Only the rare food is worth trying, beef yakiniku was great though
Service here is sub-standard.
I like Shake Chazuke

Great place for Sushi! No tourists on Monday nights, just locals. :) #HiddenGem
The scallop sushi -$9 for this plate 😳. Itacho's is bigger an cheaper!! Here is petite pieces!
The raw fish slices are the thickest, freshest and most buttery i've tried in any Jap restaurant in SG. Yumz!

Nice selection of sushi. A bit expensive but very delicious.

Good deal and great place for set meal. Nippon style

Try the new set menu! And the swordfish sashimi is orgasmic!

Price vs Quality.... Don't think it is worth it...
King Prawn Maki - 👍 must try!

Excellent salmon sashimi! The sushi from the special menu is very good too!

Tue night good - sashimi 50% off, beer cheap, food is sensational for taste & value for money. If doing a walk-in, get there early ie before 7pm. I am leaving at 7:30 and it is full.

best make a reservation or you'll have to wait awhile before being seated.

monday madness: go early to queue!! it was a long queue but food and prices are worth it. although service was rushed but that was understandable.
Great sushi, sets are more filling than they look. BYO serviette/napkins.
Bence deneyin

Rolls are better than sashimi and nigiri. Rolls half price on Wednesdays.

Sake! Plum wine!! 50% nomnomom

Good food n good service from Crystal n Yvonne

Tamago Sushi - pretty isn't it?

15% discount for Stanchart credit card holders. Not sure how long is promo for (ask d cashier)

Try the Sashimi Set, and their ala-carte items are very yummy too!
